# ============================================================================
# CREATIVEIQ (CREATIVE INTELLIGENCE PLATFORM) — CURSOR RULES
# ============================================================================
# Project: CreativeIQ — Creative Intelligence Layer for Ad Optimization
# Stack: Python 3.12 | FastAPI | Google Cloud Platform | Gemini | Snowflake
# Author: Bhargavi | Weekly Weights
# ============================================================================

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PROJECT OVERVIEW
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This is a production-grade agentic creative intelligence platform that:
# 1. Ingests video ads from multiple sources (uploads, Meta Ad Library, TikTok)
# 2. Decomposes each ad into 30+ measurable creative attributes using
#    Gemini multimodal AI, ffmpeg, cv2, and librosa
# 3. Links creative attributes to ad performance data
# 4. Builds per-brand creative profiles that learn what works over time
# 5. Provides a conversational AI interface (LangGraph) for brand managers
#    to interact with the intelligence layer
# 6. Designs and analyzes A/B tests with statistical rigor
# 7. Generates optimized creative briefs based on accumulated brand knowledge
#
# The system maintains three types of knowledge:
# - Quantitative Intelligence (Snowflake + dbt — attribute-performance scores)
# - Contextual Memory (Postgres + pgvector — brand timeline, events, eras)
# - Collaborative Reasoning (LangGraph chat — human-AI strategic dialogue)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TECH STACK — STRICTLY ENFORCED
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Language:        Python 3.12 (all services)
# Framework:       FastAPI (async, type-annotated)
# AI/LLM:          Google Gemini 2.5 Pro/Flash (ALL LLM calls)
# Orchestration:   LangGraph (multi-agent pipelines)
# Database:        Cloud SQL for PostgreSQL 16 + pgvector extension
# Data Warehouse:  Snowflake (analytical queries, dbt models)
# Transforms:      dbt-core with dbt-snowflake adapter
# Object Storage:  Google Cloud Storage (GCS)
# Cache/Queue:     Memorystore for Redis
# Task Queue:      Celery with Redis broker
# Pipeline Orch:   Cloud Composer (managed Airflow)
# Containers:      Docker + GKE (Google Kubernetes Engine)
# Registry:        Artifact Registry (Docker images: creativeiq-api, etc.)
# IaC:             Terraform (GCP provider)
# CI/CD:           GitHub Actions → Artifact Registry → GKE
# Monitoring:      Prometheus + Grafana + Cloud Logging
# Video Processing: ffmpeg, OpenCV (cv2), librosa
# Transcription:   Whisper (local) or Gemini audio
# Auth:            JWT + Google Cloud IAM (RBAC)
# Frontend:        React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
#
# DO NOT introduce AWS services (S3, RDS, EKS, Lambda, SQS, etc.)
# DO NOT use OpenAI or Anthropic APIs for any LLM calls
# DO NOT use LangChain — use LangGraph directly
# DO NOT use MongoDB, DynamoDB, or any NoSQL database as primary store

