# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PYTHON CODING STANDARDS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Type hints on ALL function signatures — no exceptions
# 2. Use Pydantic v2 models for all data validation and serialization
# 3. Use async/await for all I/O-bound operations
# 4. Use SQLAlchemy 2.0 style (select(), not legacy query())
# 5. Use structured logging with structlog — no print() statements
# 6. All env config through Pydantic Settings — no os.getenv() in code
# 7. Explicit try/except with typed exceptions — never bare except
# 8. Google-style docstrings on all public functions
# 9. No wildcard imports (from x import *)
# 10. Max function length: ~50 lines. Decompose if longer.
# 11. Use pathlib.Path — not os.path
# 12. Use datetime from standard lib with timezone-aware objects (UTC)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# FASTAPI PATTERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - All routes return Pydantic response models — never raw dicts
# - Use Depends() for auth, db sessions, shared dependencies
# - Use APIRouter per resource, grouped in routes/ directory
# - All endpoints have explicit status_code and response_model
# - Background tasks for anything >500ms
# - WebSocket for chat with proper connection lifecycle
# - Health check at /health and /ready for k8s probes
# - CORS locked to frontend domain only
# - Versioned API prefix: /api/v1/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DATABASE PATTERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - Alembic for ALL schema migrations — never raw DDL
# - UUIDs as primary keys (uuid7 for time-sortable, generated in Python)
# - JSONB for flexible schemas (fingerprints, profiles, metadata)
# - pgvector for semantic search over brand memory
# - Parameterized queries only — no f-string SQL
# - Indexes on: brand_id, platform, created_at, ad_id
# - Soft deletes with deleted_at — never hard delete user data
# - Connection pooling via SQLAlchemy async engine
# - Separate read replica connection for heavy queries

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GEMINI API PATTERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - ALL LLM calls route through shared/utils/gemini.py
# - Gemini 2.5 Pro: decomposition, strategy, complex analysis
# - Gemini 2.5 Flash: classification, embeddings, simple tasks
# - Always request JSON output via response_mime_type="application/json"
# - Retry with exponential backoff: 3 attempts, base=1s
# - Log token usage per call to Prometheus metrics
# - temperature=0 for analytical, 0.7 for creative generation
# - Sanitize all user input before sending to Gemini
# - Cache identical requests in Redis (TTL: 24h)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GCS BUCKET STRUCTURE
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# gs://ci-{env}-raw-ads/{brand_id}/{ad_id}/original.mp4
# gs://ci-{env}-extracted/{ad_id}/frames/frame_001.jpg
# gs://ci-{env}-extracted/{ad_id}/audio/audio.wav
# gs://ci-{env}-models/{brand_id}/{platform}/statistical_profile.json
# gs://ci-{env}-models/{brand_id}/{platform}/lgbm_model.pkl
# gs://ci-{env}-brand-assets/{brand_id}/guidelines/
# gs://ci-{env}-exports/{user_id}/
#
# - Use signed URLs for frontend access (15 min expiry)
# - Object versioning on raw-ads bucket
# - Lifecycle: extracted frames → Nearline after 30 days
# Phase 1 local MinIO: create only the four buckets (raw, extracted, models, brand-assets) per PHASE_1_SPEC.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LANGGRAPH PATTERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - State as TypedDict with all required context fields
# - Each agent = one graph node with single responsibility
# - Conditional edges for routing decisions
# - Tools with @tool decorator and clear docstrings
# - Conversation history in state, persisted to Postgres
# - Max 5 tool calls per agent turn before returning
# - Brand context (profile + timeline) always in agent state

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# dbt PATTERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - staging/: 1:1 with sources. Only rename, cast, clean.
# - intermediate/: joins, business logic, no aggregations
# - marts/: final analytical tables for consumption
# - Every model has schema.yml with descriptions + tests
# - Incremental models for ads, performance, fingerprints
# - Source freshness checks on raw tables
# - Tags: staging, intermediate, marts, tests

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CELERY TASK PATTERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - One task per file, descriptive name: decompose_ad, compute_profile
# - Always set soft_time_limit and time_limit
# - Task chains: ingest → decompose → update_profile → notify
# - Exponential backoff on transient failures
# - Dead letter queue for permanently failed tasks
# - Task state tracked in Postgres for UI visibility

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TERRAFORM PATTERNS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - One module per GCP resource type
# - Environment separation: dev.tfvars, prod.tfvars
# - State in GCS bucket with locking
# - No hardcoded values — everything parameterized
# - Workload Identity for GKE pods (no SA keys)
# - Private GKE cluster with authorized networks
# - Cloud SQL: private IP only, require SSL
# - All GCS buckets: uniform access, no public access

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECURITY REQUIREMENTS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - No credentials in code — Secret Manager + Workload Identity
# - Least privilege IAM per service
# - JWT: 15-min access token, 7-day refresh token
# - Rate limiting on public endpoints (Redis-based)
# - Input validation on all user inputs
# - HTTPS only — all environments
# - VPC-native GKE with network policies between services
# - Audit logging on all GCP resources
# - CMEK encryption on Cloud SQL and GCS if needed

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TESTING
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - pytest for all tests
# - Unit: mock external services (Gemini, GCS, Snowflake)
# - Integration: testcontainers for Postgres + Redis
# - Coverage target: 80% on shared/ and business logic
# - Fixtures for test data (sample ads, fingerprints, profiles)
# - factory_boy for test object generation

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GIT CONVENTIONS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - Branches: feature/{phase}-{desc}, fix/{desc}, chore/{desc}
# - Commits: conventional (feat:, fix:, docs:, refactor:, test:)
# - PR required for main — no direct pushes
# - Squash merge for clean history

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DO NOT
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# - Use Jupyter notebooks for production code
# - Use pandas in services (use Polars if needed for data processing)
# - Use print() — use structlog
# - Hardcode credentials, URLs, or env-specific values
# - Create 500+ line files or god classes
# - Use global mutable state
# - Skip type hints
# - Use sync DB calls in async endpoints
# - Store binary files in the database
# - Write raw SQL in app code — use SQLAlchemy ORM or dbt
